    &lt;CommentText&gt;Thank you for taking the time to post your comments regarding your recent experience.

Firstly may I take this opportunity to sincerely apologise for the experience you received when you accompanied your wife for a blood test.  What you have described does not meet the Trust values in terms of respect and caring.  

It is clear from your posting how frustrated you have been left feeling and again, I am sorry for both you and your wife’s experience.  It is important that we receive feedback so that we can learn from our patient’s experience.

There are a number of areas you mention that cause me concern and I have shared your feedback with the Manager of the service so that they can address the issues you’ve highlighted with their staff.  

Thank you again.

Kind regards
Clare Blackburn
